Data Fields

uint8_t subFrameIdx
 Sub-frame index, this is in the range [0..numSubFrames - 1]. This is the sub-frame whose results have been exported. Although this DPC implementation knows what sub-frame to expect as the exports are expected to be sequential in sub-frames, this field helps in error checking when for example the application could miss exporting/consuming a sub-frame in a timely manner or have out of order export/consumption. Field Documentation

uint8_t DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResultExportedInfo_t::subFrameIdx

Sub-frame index, this is in the range [0..numSubFrames - 1]. This is the sub-frame whose results have been exported. Although this DPC implementation knows what sub-frame to expect as the exports are expected to be sequential in sub-frames, this field helps in error checking when for example the application could miss exporting/consuming a sub-frame in a timely manner or have out of order export/consumption.
